comments: Banchero (ORL) initiates contact with Johnson's (ATL) arm, which affects Johnson's SQBR.
Johnson (ATL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.

Suggs (ORL) makes contact with Capela's (ATL) head, which affects his ability to pursue the rebound. Capela never has full control of the ball prior to the illegal contact, and a loose ball foul is correctly called.
Banchero (ORL) enters the lane prior to Capela (ATL) releasing the free throw attempt.
Banchero (ORL) goes through Johnson (ATL), who is established in his path, and dislodges Johnson from his legally obtained position.
Banchero (ORL) initiates contact with Young's (ATL) head, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Capela (ATL) brings his arm toward Wagner's (ORL) path and marginal contact occurs at the start of Wagner's drive toward the basket.
Capela (ATL) moves alongside Wagner's (ORL) path and maintains a legal guarding position as incidental contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Wagner (ORL) brings his hands toward Hunter (ATL) and marginal contact occurs as Wagner releases away to cut toward the perimeter.
Murray (ATL) legally contests Banchero's (ORL) jump shot attempt.
After gaining control of the loose ball, Fultz (ORL) does not step out of bounds as his left foot hovers above the baseline out of bounds before releasing his pass.
